## âš™ï¸ Getting Started

### 1) Clone
```bash
git clone https://github.com/jake1318/Poseidon-s-Catch.git
cd Poseidon-s-Catch

2) Install
# Frontend
cd client
npm install

# Backend
cd ../server
npm install

3) Configure env

Create server/.env:

PORT=4000
DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"     # SQLite for local dev OR your Postgres/MySQL URL
# EMAIL_SMTP_URL=...             # optional if you send confirmation emails


If youâ€™re using SQLite, generate the DB (example with Prisma):

# if Prisma is used
npx prisma migrate dev --name init
npx prisma db seed # optional

4) Run the app
# Backend
cd server
npm run dev          # starts API at http://localhost:4000

# Frontend (in a second terminal)
cd ../client
npm run dev          # starts Vite at http://localhost:5173

ğŸ”Œ API Overview

All routes prefixed by /api from the frontend.

Menu

GET /api/menu â€” list menu items

GET /api/menu/:id â€” get single item

Reviews

GET /api/reviews â€” list reviews

POST /api/reviews â€” create { name, rating, comment }

PUT /api/reviews/:id â€” update (if enabled)

DELETE /api/reviews/:id â€” delete (if enabled)

Reservations

POST /api/reservations â€” create { name, email, phone, partySize, date, time, note? }

GET /api/reservations?date=YYYY-MM-DD â€” list for a day (admin view)

Optional email or on-screen confirmation

Validation: server enforces date/time in the future, reasonable party size, and contact info. Conflict checks can be added to prevent overbooking.

ğŸ§ª Scripts

Common scripts you may have (adjust to your package.json):

{
  "client": {
    "scripts": {
      "dev": "vite",
      "build": "vite build",
      "preview": "vite preview"
    }
  },
  "server": {
    "scripts": {
      "dev": "ts-node-dev --respawn src/index.ts",
      "build": "tsc -p .",
      "start": "node dist/index.js"
    }
  }
}
